**End‑to‑End Integration Test Scenario**  
*DOE Integrated Weapon‑Storage Safety System – Contract DE‑NA0004385*  
*Facility: Pantex Plant – Q‑clearance, Sigma 1‑4*  

The scenario exercises the full chain that starts with a degrading containment seal, proceeds through autonomous emergency‑response logic, creates a TPI‑waiver, grants single‑person access, delivers AR‑guided work instructions, and temporarily suppresses tamper‑detection alarms.  
All calls are made over mutually‑authenticated TLS 1.3, carry a JSON‑Web‑Token (JWT) signed by the site PKI, and are logged to the immutable Secure Audit Log (SAL).  

---

## 1. Assumptions & Preconditions  

| Item | Value / State |
|------|----------------|
| **Sensor S‑7** (containment‑seal strain gauge) reports a **positive, accelerating strain rate** that the degradation‑prediction model maps to a **projected atmospheric release in 90 min** if unchecked. |
| **Current crew**: one technician **T‑1** (TPI‑certified, Sigma 3) physically present in the vault‑access corridor. |
| **Second‑nearest TPI‑certified responder** (**T‑2**) is **3 h** away by air (estimated arrival > 180 min). |
| **TPI‑Response‑Time (TRT)** for a second qualified person = **180 min** (worst‑case travel + badge‑validation). |
| **Projected Threat Window (PTW)** = **90 min** (time to exceed 10 CFR 835 limit). |
| **Condition for single‑person access**: `TRT > PTW` → **true** (180 > 90). |
| **Tamper‑Detection System (TDS)** is armed and would normally alarm on any single‑person vault entry. |
| **AR headset** (Microsoft HoloLens 2) is paired to the technician’s badge and subscribed to the `/ar/instructions` stream. |
| **All services** (AER, SPEA, ACS, AR, TDS, SAL) are healthy and have valid mutual‑TLS certificates. |

---

## 2. Core Data Models (excerpt)

```protobuf
// 1. AER trigger (produced by the degradation‑prediction + rate‑of‑change engine)
message AERTrigger {
  string trigger_id = 1;                         // UUID
  google.protobuf.Timestamp ts = 2;
  float projected_dose_rate = 3;                 // Sv/h (projected at PTW)
  uint32 ptw_minutes = 4;                        // Projected Threat Window
  uint32 trt_minutes = 5;                        // Estimated TPI‑Response‑Time
}

// 2. TPI waiver (produced by SPEA)
message TpiWaiver {
  string waiver_id = 1;                          // UUID
  string trigger_id = 2;                         // links to AERTrigger
  google.protobuf.Timestamp issued_ts = 3;
  string justification = 4;                      // free‑text, auto‑filled
  uint32 ptw_minutes = 5;
  uint32 trt_minutes = 6;
  bytes signature = 7;                           // RSA‑4096, SHA‑384 over fields 1‑6
}

// 3. Emergency Access Token (EAT) – issued by ACS
message EmergencyAccessToken {
  string token_id = 1;                           // UUID, one‑time use
  string subject_id = 2;                         // technician badge ID
  google.protobuf.Timestamp valid_from = 3;
  google.protobuf.Timestamp valid_until = 4;     // short‑lived (≤ 15 min)
  repeated string allowed_doors = 5;             // e.g., ["VAULT‑DOOR‑03"]
  repeated string allowed_actions = 6;           // e.g., ["OPEN", "CLOSE"]
  bytes signature = 7;                           // ACS private key
}

// 4. AR instruction packet
message ArInstruction {
  string instruction_id = 1;
  string workflow_id = 2;                        // links to work‑order / waiver
  string step_number = 3;
  string description = 4;                        // human‑readable
  string model_uri = 5;                          // URI to 3‑D overlay (glTF)
  string audio_uri = 6;                          // optional voice prompt
}

// 5. Tamper‑suppression request
message TamperSuppressRequest {
  string request_id = 1;
  string waiver_id = 2;                          // ties suppression to waiver
  google.protobuf.Timestamp start_ts = 3;
  google.protobuf.Timestamp end_ts = 4;          // auto‑expires after max 30 min
  string reason = 5;                             // e.g., "Single‑person emergency access per waiver"
  bytes signature = 6;
}
```

